20War%2C%20in%20the%201950s%2C%20the%20West%20worried%20that%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20and%20China%20had%20joined%20forces%20to%20form%20a%20massive%20Communist%20bloc.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20those%20fears%20proved%20overblown%2C%20as%20Beijing%20and%20Moscow%20soon%20went%20from%20allies%20to%20bitter%20enemies%20that%20clashed%20over%20their%20long%20border.%20Fast%20forward%20to%20today%2C%20and%20growing%20military%20ties%20have%20again%20raised%20the%20specter%20of%20a%20Sino-Russian%20alliance%20that%20unites%20two%20of%20the%20most%20powerful%20nations%20in%20the%20world.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20this%20partnership%20is%20not%20a%20solid%20alliance%20like%20NATO%20that's%20built%20on%20mutual%20defense%20and%20interoperability%20of%20its%20forces.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Sino-Russian%20relationship%20is%20probably%20best%20characterized%20as%20a%20marriage%20of%20two%20imperfect%20partners%20who%20share%20a%20deeply%20cynical%20view%20of%20the%20U.S.-led%20international%20order%20but%20often%20hold%20divergent%20visions%20of%20the%20order%20that%20they%20believe%20should%20replace%20it%2C%26quot%3B%20according%20to%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.rand.org%2Fpubs%2Fresearch_reports%2FRRA2061-5.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Ereport%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20Sino-Russian%20cooperation%20by%20the%20RAND%20Corp.%20think%20tank.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BThese%20two%20imperfect%20partners%20realize%20some%20level%20of%20shared%2C%20albeit%20unequal%2C%20dependency%20while%20simultaneously%20harboring%20deep%20suspicions%20about%20whether%20they%20can%20trust%20or%20rely%20on%20the%20other%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20study%20said.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThis%20may%20be%20scant%20comfort%20to%20Western%20leaders%20who%20fear%20a%20scenario%20where%20Russian%20aggression%20in%20Europe%20is%20simultaneous%20with%20a%20Chinese%20invasion%20of%20Taiwan%2C%20which%20would%20overstretch%20US%20resources%20and%20allow%20America's%20allies%20to%20be%20overwhelmed.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EAlready%2C%20Russia's%20military%20and%20China's%20People's%20Liberation%20Army%20have%20held%20around%2025%20joint%20exercises%20since%202005%2C%20involving%20ships%2C%20aircraft%20and%20ground%20troops.%20Beijing%20and%20Moscow%20have%20teamed%20up%20to%20fly%20joint%20patrols%2C%20including%20a%202023%20incident%20where%20they%20flew%20near%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.cbsnews.com%2Fnews%2Fsouth-korea-china-russia-north-korea-warplanes-air-defense-zone%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3ESouth%20Korean%20airspace%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EEqually%20important%20is%20that%20China%20has%20become%20a%20key%20enabler%20of%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine.%20With%20Western%20sanctions%20depriving%20Russia%20of%20key%20components%20such%20as%20electronics%2C%20China%20and%20its%20vast%20manufacturing%20base%20have%20emerged%20as%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.forbes.com%2Fsites%2Fbrianbushard%2F2024%2F04%2F12%2Fchina-sending-russia-missile-and-drone-parts-for-ukraine-war-us-reportedly-warns%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Emajor%20supplier%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20of%20microelectronics%2C%20drone%20parts%2C%20and%20other%20components.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBut%20these%20don't%20equate%20to%20the%20sort%20of%20integrated%20operations%20practiced%20by%20the%20US%20and%20Britain%20in%20World%20War%20II%2C%20where%20American%20troops%20served%20under%20British%20commanders%20and%20vice%20versa%2C%20or%20by%20NATO%20today.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BPolicymakers%20and%20planners%20should%20avoid%20overestimating%20the%20state%20of%20military%20cooperation%20and%20operational%20integration%20that%20exists%20between%20Russia%20and%20China%2C%26quot%3B%20RAND%20warned.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cfigure%3E%3Cimg%20width%3D%5C%222000%5C%22%20alt%3D%5C%22China%20sent%20only%20a%20few%20thousand%20troops%20to%20Russia's%20massive%202018%20war%20game%20of%20an%20estimated%20300%2C000%20participants.%5C%22%20charset%3D%5C%22%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fi.insider.com%2F667eea4540cf2af6e4f6cb56%3Fformat%3Djpeg%5C%22%20height%3D%5C%221345%5C%22%3E%3Cfigcaption%3EChina%20sent%20only%20a%20few%20thousand%20troops%20to%20Russia's%20massive%202018%20war%20game%20of%20an%20estimated%20300%2C000%20participants.%3Cp%3EMladen%20Antonov%2FGetty%20Images%3C%2Fp%3E%3C%2Ffigcaption%3E%3C%2Ffigure%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EExercises%20involving%20Russian%20and%20Chinese%20forces%20have%20been%20%26quot%3Bdescribed%20as%20more%20'parallel'%20than%20'joint%2C'%20meaning%20that%20Russia's%20military%20and%20the%20PLA%20are%20given%20set%20tasks%20and%20timelines%2C%20perform%20them%20in%20synchronized%20yet%20independent%20fashion%2C%20and%20overall%20have%20limited%20interaction%20in%20such%20areas%20as%20planning%20and%20C2%20%5Bcommand%20and%20control%5D%2C%26quot%3B%20RAND%20said.%20%26quot%3BFor%20this%20reason%2C%20these%20exercises%20have%20in%20reality%20done%20relatively%20little%20to%20promote%20interoperability%20at%20either%20the%20operational%20or%20the%20tactical%20level.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EThe%20result%20is%20military%20cooperation%20that%20is%20more%20symbolic%20than%20practical.%20%26quot%3BChina's%20commitment%20to%20the%20exercises%20is%20relatively%20low%2C%26quot%3B%20RAND%20said.%20%26quot%3BThe%20PLA%20%5BPeople's%20Liberation%20Army%5D%20sent%20around%203%2C200%20soldiers%20to%20Russia's%20300%2C000-strong%20Vostok%202018%20exercise%20and%20just%201%2C600%20to%20Russia's%20Tsentr-2019%20exercise%20(in%20which%20the%20Russian%20side%20fielded%20almost%20130%2C000%20soldiers).%20It%20appears%20that%20the%20PLA%20is%20more%20interested%20in%20learning%20from%20Russia%20than%20in%20sharing%20insights%20into%20its%20own%20military%20capabilities%20or%20training%20as%20equal%20partners%2C%20whereas%2C%20for%20Russia%2C%20the%20goal%20is%20to%20present%20an%20image%20of%20joint%20cooperation%20with%20China%20to%20the%20West%20to%20counter%20an%20impression%20that%20Moscow%20is%20isolated%20and%20vulnerable.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EMark%20Cozad%2C%20who%20co-authored%20the%20RAND%20study%2C%20contrasted%20these%20arrangements%20with%20NATO%20or%20US-South%20Korean%20military%20integration.%20%26quot%3BNATO%20and%20the%20US-South%20Korea%20plan%20to%20fight%20as%20alliances%20which%20means%20that%20training%20needs%20to%20develop%20and%20train%20combined%20command%20and%20control%2C%20targeting%2C%20ISR%20%5Bintelligence%20and%20reconnaissance%5D%2C%20logistics%2C%20and%20operations%20among%20other%20areas%2C%26quot%3B%20Cozad%20told%20Business%20Insider.%20%26quot%3BAlso%2C%20there%20is%20a%20much%20more%20rigorous%20approach%20to%20training%20in%20these%20alliances%20meaning%20the%20training%20is%20generally%20much%20more%20realistic%20than%20what%20we%20see%20out%20of%20the%20Russians%20and%20Chinese.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EDespite%20boasting%20of%20their%20military%20ties%2C%20Russia%20and%20China%20don't%20have%20much%20faith%20in%20each%20other's%20military%20prowess.%20After%20Russia's%20dismal%20combat%20performance%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20the%20question%20is%20%26quot%3Bwhether%20China%20would%20view%20the%20Russian%20military%20as%20a%20capable%20and%20useful%20coalition%20partner%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20said.%20On%20the%20other%20hand%2C%20given%20China's%20lack%20of%20recent%20combat%20experience%2C%20%26quot%3BMoscow%20may%20view%20the%20PLA%20as%20a%20well-resourced%20but%20questionable%20partner.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESome%20alliances%20are%20tighter%20than%20others.%20America%20and%20Britain%20were%20part%20of%20the%20Grand%20Alliance%20with%20the%20Soviet%20Union%2C%20in%20which%20Russia%20and%20the%20Western%20Allies%20waged%20parallel%20and%20mostly%20uncoordinated%20campaigns%20in%20an%20atmosphere%20of%20mutual%20distrust.%20Capitalist%20and%20Communist%20could%20agree%20on%20the%20need%20to%20defeat%20Hitler%2C%20but%20not%20much%20else.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20their%202001%20friendship%20treaty%2C%20China%20and%20Russia%20did%20agree%20to%20consult%20with%20each%20other%20should%20either%20nation%20be%20attacked.%20But%20they%20didn't%20promise%20to%20fight%20on%20each%20other's%20behalf.%20%26quot%3BNotably%2C%20this%20agreement%20does%20not%20include%20a%20mutual%20defense%20clause%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20RAND%20study%20pointed%20out.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3ESuccessful%20alliances%20require%20partners%20to%20subordinate%20their%20interests%20for%20the%20good%20of%20the%20alliance%2C%20and%20that's%20a%20huge%20problem%20for%20Russia%20and%20China.%20Both%20nations%20have%20a%20tradition%20of%20being%20the%20dominant%20partner%20in%20alliances%20and%20of%20bullying%20their%20allies%2C%20whether%20it%20was%20the%20Soviet%20Union%20bossing%20their%20Eastern%20European%20satellites%2C%20or%20China%20treating%20neighbors%20such%20as%20Vietnam%20and%20Korea%20as%20vassals.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3E%26quot%3BNeither%20China%20nor%20Russia%20has%20a%20recent%20history%20of%20an%20interoperable%20military%20alliance%20with%20any%20other%20country%2C%20much%20less%20any%20history%20of%20joint%20C2%20%5Bcommand%20and%20control%5D%20structures%20or%20devolving%20authority%20to%20field%20commanders%20to%20innovate%20and%20partner%20to%20solve%20operational%20challenges%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20the%20report.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EBesides%20the%20pleasure%20of%20driving%20America%20crazy%2C%20military%20cooperation%20between%20China%20and%20Russia%20does%20offer%20tangible%20benefits.%20China%2C%20which%20has%20not%20fought%20a%20war%20since%20invading%20Vietnam%20in%201979%2C%20can%20learn%20from%20Russian%20combat%20experience%20in%20Syria%20and%20Ukraine.%20Russia%20gets%20access%20to%20Chinese%20products%20that%20are%20under%20sanction%20in%20the%20West.%20Good%20relations%20means%20the%202%2C600-mile-long%20Russia-China%20border%20can%20be%20demilitarized%2C%20allowing%20forces%20to%20be%20concentrated%20in%20Ukraine%20or%20for%20an%20invasion%20of%20Taiwan.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EYet%20there%20are%20plenty%20of%20issues%20that%20could%20derail%20this%20alliance.%20One%20is%20the%20immense%20amount%20of%20historical%20baggage%20weighing%20down%20their%20relations.%20%26quot%3BThe%20Russians%20and%20Chinese%20have%20had%20a%20mixed%20relationship%20for%20over%2075%20years%20at%20this%20point%20that%20has%20included%20both%20strategic%20partnership%20and%20intense%20hostility%2C%26quot%3B%20Cozad%20noted.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EChina%20hasn't%20forgotten%20that%20Tsarist%20Russia%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fchinamediaproject.org%2F2023%2F03%2F24%2Fon-national-humiliation-dont-mention-the-russians%2F%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eannexed%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20350%2C000%20square%20miles%20of%20Chinese%20territory%20in%20the%201850s.%20In%201969%2C%20Chinese%20and%20Russian%20troops%20fought%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22about%3Ablank%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Eborder%20clashes%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20along%20the%20Ussuri%20River%20(at%20one%20point%2C%20the%20Soviets%20considered%20a%20%3C%2Fspan%3E%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.telegraph.co.uk%2Fnews%2Fworldnews%2Fasia%2Fchina%2F7720461%2FUSSR-planned-nuclear-attack-on-China-in-1969.html%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3E%3Cspan%3Enuclear%20strike%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fa%3E%3Cspan%3E%20on%20China).%20Today%2C%20there%20is%20competition%20over%20Central%20Asia%2C%20Chinese%20unease%20over%20Russia's%20war%20in%20Ukraine%2C%20and%20the%20fact%20that%20Russia%20is%20inexorably%20becoming%20the%20junior%20partner%20as%20Chinese%20economic%20and%20military%20power%20grows.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EWhich%20raises%20the%20question%3A%20can%20the%20West%20exploit%20these%20potential%20divisions%20to%20break%20up%20the%20Sino-Russian%20alliance%3F%20RAND%20emphatically%20warns%20against%20trying.%20%26quot%3BWe%20advocate%20not%20trying%20to%20undermine%20the%20Russia-China%20partnership%20because%20we%20don't%20have%20many%20tools%20or%20incentives%20that%20either%20of%20those%20two%20partners%20sees%20as%20more%20valuable%20than%20their%20partnership%2C%26quot%3B%20Cozad%20said.%20While%20the%20Chinese%20may%20want%20things%20from%20the%20US%2C%20%26quot%3Bthey%20are%20skeptical%20that%20in%20five%20or%2010%20years%20that%20incentive%20can%20again%20be%20taken%20away%20and%20then%20they%20have%20damaged%20their%20relationship%20with%20Russia%20while%20losing%20that%20incentive.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EInstead%2C%20RAND%20suggests%20that%20the%20best%20response%20would%20be%20for%20the%20US%20and%20its%20allies%20to%20ally%20more%20closely.%20%26quot%3BThe%20most%20effective%20way%20for%20the%20United%20States%20to%20counter%20the%20Russia-China%20strategic%20partnership%20is%20by%20ensuring%20the%20health%20of%20its%20own%20alliances%20and%20pursuing%20ever%20greater%20cooperation%20with%20its%20most%20important%20allies%20and%20partners%2C%26quot%3B%20the%20report%20recommended.%3C%2Fspan%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cspan%3EIn%20the%20end%2C%20successful%20alliances%20are%20a%20mixture%20not%20just%20of%20national%20self-interest%2C%20but%20of%20shared%20values.%20That%20may%20be%20the%20real%20difference%20between%20an%20alliance%20like%20NATO%2C%20most%20of%20whose%20members%20share%20a%20belief%20in%20democracy%2C%20individual%20rights%20and%20free%20trade%2C%20versus%20a%20Sino-Russian%20friendship%20based%20on%20the%20question%20of%20%26quot%3Bwhat's%20in%20it%20for%20me.%26quot%3B