oped%20countries%2C%20the%20spending%20behaviour%20of%20people%20has%20significantly%20changed.%20A%20study%20conducted%20by%20a%20team%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Adelaide%20and%20the%20University%20of%20Melbourne%20in%20Australia%20has%20concluded%20that%20cashless%20payments%20are%20driving%20people%20to%20spend%20more%20than%20before.%20The%20researchers%20conducted%20the%20study%20by%20doing%20a%20meta-analysis%20of%2071%20previous%20papers%20and%20by%20observing%20the%20spending%20habits%20of%20people%20across%2017%20countries.%20They%20found%20that%20the%20convenience%20of%20spending%20has%20made%20people%20more%20prone%20to%20spending%20on%20luxurious%20items%20that%20are%20mostly%20unnecessary.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BTo%20prevent%20spending%20more%20than%20planned%2C%20we%20recommend%20consumers%20carry%20cash%20instead%20of%20cards%20whenever%20they%20can%2C%20as%20it%20acts%20as%20a%20self-control%20method%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20marketing%20researcher%20Lachlan%20Schomburgk%20from%20the%20University%20of%20Adelaide%2C%20as%20per%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.sciencealert.com%2Fcashless-payments-are-changing-our-spending-behavior-study-reveals%5C%22%3E%3Cem%3EScience%20Alert%3C%2Fem%3E%3C%2Fa%3E.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20using%20cash%2C%20people%20physically%20count%20and%20hand%20over%20notes%20and%20coins%2C%20making%20the%20act%20of%20spending%20more%20salient.%20If%20nothing%20is%20physically%20handed%20over%2C%20it's%20easy%20to%20lose%20track%20of%20how%20much%20is%20spent%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20study%2C%20researchers%20noted%20that%20the%20link%20between%20high%20spending%20and%20cashless%20payments%20has%20been%20visible%20for%20a%20long%20time.%20However%2C%20they%20added%20that%20it%20is%20the%20first%20time%20that%20the%20spending%20behaviour%20of%20people%20has%20been%20tracked%20at%20this%20scale.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EAlso%20Read%20%7C%C2%A0%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fscience%2Fdaily-multivitamin-supplements-do-not-help-you-live-longer-study-finds-5986654%5C%22%3EDaily%20Multivitamin%20Supplements%20Do%20Not%20Help%20You%20Live%20Longer%2C%20Study%20Finds%3C%2Fa%3E%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20difference%20in%20spending%20was%20%26quot%3Bsmall%2C%20but%20significant%26quot%3B%20the%20researchers%20said.%20It%20was%20greater%20for%20%26quot%3Bconspicuous%20consumption%26quot%3B%20spending%2C%20which%20is%20buying%20items%20that%20signal%20status%20-%20so%20luxury%20clothing%20and%20jewellery%2C%20for%20example.%20The%20team%20also%20observed%20that%20digital%20payments%20do%20not%20affect%20tips%20or%20donations.%20People%20spend%20money%20on%20donations%20as%20much%20as%20they%20used%20to%20with%20cash%2C%20they%20added.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BAgainst%20our%20expectations%2C%20we%20found%20that%20cashless%20payments%20do%20not%20necessarily%20lead%20to%20greater%20tips%20or%20donations%2C%20in%20comparison%20to%20cash%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Schomburgk.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFurther%2C%20the%20team%20of%20researchers%20found%20a%20link%20between%20more%20positive%20economic%20conditions%20and%20a%20greater%20cashless%20effect.%20They%20also%20found%20the%20cashless%20effect%20has%20gotten%20weaker%20over%20time%2C%20suggesting%20that%20as%20cashless%20payment%20methods%20have%20become%20more%20common%2C%20they%20have%20less%20impact%20on%20consumers.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20transition%20towards%20a%20cashless%20society%20seems%20almost%20inevitable.%20I%20believe%20this%20research%20is%20crucial%20because%20it%20shines%20a%20light%20on%20an%20overlooked%20aspect%20of%20this%20transition%3A%20how%20payment%20methods%20influence%20our%20spending%20behaviour%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Mr%20Schomburgk.%20%26quot%3BThis%20understanding%20can%20help%20empower%20us%20to%20make%20more%20informed%20purchasing%20decisions%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20added.%C2%A0