2engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22US%20military%20destroys%20seven%20drones%2C%20vehicle%20in%20Yemen's%20Houthi-control%20region%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719639241000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fstatic.toiimg.com%2Fphoto%2Fmsid-111356793%2Cimgsize-30152.cms%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-military-destroys-seven-drones-vehicle-in-yemens-houthi-control-region%2Farticleshow%2F111356756.cms%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22%3Cimg%20border%3D%5C%220%5C%22%20align%3D%5C%22left%5C%22%20src%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fphoto%2F111356756.cms%5C%22%20hspace%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3EOver%20the%20past%2024%20hours%2C%20US%20forces%20have%20destroyed%20seven%20drones%20and%20a%20control%20station%20vehicle%20in%20areas%20of%20Yemen%20controlled%20by%20the%20Huthis.%20The%20US%20Central%20Command%20stated%20that%20the%20strikes%20were%20carried%20out%20in%20response%20to%20an%20imminent%20threat%20to%20US%20coalition%20forces%20and%20merchant%20vessels%20in%20the%20region.%20The%20Huthis%20are%20an%20Iran-backed%20group%20that%20has%20been%20targeting%20vessels%20in%20the%20Red%20Sea%20and%20Gulf%20of%20Aden%20since%20November%202023.%20They%20claim%20their%20attacks%20are%20in%20solidarity%20with%20Palestinians%20during%20the%20Israel-Hamas%20war%20in%20the%20Gaza%20Strip.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22TOI%20World%20Desk%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-military-destroys-seven-drones-vehicle-in-yemens-houthi-control-region%2Farticleshow%2F111356756.cms%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia-indiatimes-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-military-destroys-seven-drones-vehicle-in-yemens-houthi-control-region%2Famp_articleshow%2F111356756.cms%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Ftimesofindia.indiatimes.com%2Fworld%2Fus%2Fus-military-destroys-seven-drones-vehicle-in-yemens-houthi-control-region%2Famp_articleshow%2F111356756.cms%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Sunita%20Williams%20May%20Have%20To%20Wait%20Months%20In%20Space.%20What%20NASA%20Is%20Planning%20Now%22%2C%22content%22%3A%22%3Cp%3EProjected%20to%20last%20only%20days%2C%20the%20first%20crewed%20test%20flight%20of%20Boeing's%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20with%20two%20astronauts%20onboard%20faces%20uncertainty%20with%20no%20exact%20return%20to%20Earth%20announced.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA's%20Commercial%20Crew%20Program%20manager%2C%20Steve%20Stich%20has%20said%20that%20the%20US%20space%20agency%20is%20considering%20extending%20the%20duration%20of%20Starliner's%20mission%20from%2045%20days%20to%2090%20days%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOfficials%20have%20repeatedly%20hinted%20that%20the%20Starliner%2C%20which%20faced%20issues%20with%20helium%20leaks%20and%20thruster%20outages%20heading%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20in%20early%20June%2C%20will%20be%20safe%20to%20bring%20astronauts%20including%20indian-origin%20Sunita%20'Suni'%20Williams%20and%20Butch%20Wilmore%20home.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Stich%20said%20that%20NASA%20is%20considering%20extending%20the%20maximum%20length%20of%20Starliner's%20mission%20from%2045%20days%20to%2090%20days%20and%20there%20is%20no%20firm%20return%20date%20on%20the%20horizon%2C%20according%20to%20CNN%20report.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAddressing%20a%20briefing%20on%20Friday%2C%20the%20NASA%20official%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20just%20looking%20at%20the%20timeline%20to%20execute%20(the%20test%20in%20New%20Mexico)%20and%20then%20review%20the%20data.%26quot%3B%20He%20further%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BAnd%20that's%20what's%20really%20the%20long%20pole%2C%20I%20would%20say%2C%20determining%20a%20landing%20date.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStich%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BWe're%20not%20in%20a%20rush%20to%20come%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EPart%20of%20that%20desired%20extension%20is%20due%20to%20the%20ground%20tests%20that%20Boeing%20and%20NASA%20plan%20to%20conduct%20in%20New%20Mexico%2C%20seeking%20to%20better%20understand%20why%20some%20of%20the%20Starliner's%20thrusters%20unexpectedly%20failed%20during%20the%20first%20leg%20of%20its%20journey.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EStich%20and%20Mark%20Nappi%2C%20vice%20president%20and%20program%20manager%20of%20the%20Commercial%20Crew%20Program%20for%20Boeing%2C%20also%20said%20that%20engineers%20are%20still%20not%20certain%20about%20the%20reason%20behind%20the%20Starliner's%20problems.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENappi%20said%20that%20part%20of%20the%20aim%20is%20conducting%20the%20ground%20tests%20while%20the%20vehicle%20is%20still%20in%20space%20is%20to%20try%20to%20whittle%20down%20possible%20reasons%20why%20the%20thrusters%20malfunctioned.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMark%20Nappi%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BSo%2C%20if%20(the%20test%20in%20New%20Mexico)%20comes%20back%20and%20gives%20us%20all%20the%20answers%2C%20then%20we%20can%20just%20undock%20and%20come%20home.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20added%2C%20%26quot%3BIf%20it%20comes%20back%20and%20says%2C%20'Here's%2080%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20answer.%20And%20if%20you%20just%20run%20one%20more%20docked%20hot%20fire%20(test%20on%20the%20Starliner%20in%20orbit)%2C%20then%20you%20can%20get%20100%20per%20cent%20of%20the%20answers'%20--%20then%20we%20want%20(Starliner)%20to%20be%20there%20so%20that%20we%20can%20get%20that%20information.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Williams%20and%20Wilmore%20have%20integrated%20with%20the%20rest%20of%20the%20crew%20currently%20aboard%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20and%20are%20conducting%20routine%20tasks.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESeveral%20more%20helium%20leaks%20were%20identified%20while%20the%20craft%20was%20heading%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%2C%20along%20with%20the%20thruster%20issues.%20The%20Starliner's%20service%20module%2C%20a%20cylindrical%20attachment%20at%20the%20bottom%20of%20the%20spacecraft%20that%20provides%20much%20of%20the%20vehicle's%20power%20during%20flight%2C%20faced%20several%20issues%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EAs%20per%20the%20design%2C%20the%20service%20module%20will%20not%20survive%20the%20return%20to%20Earth.%20The%20module%20is%20jettisoned%20and%20destroyed%20as%20the%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20reenters%20the%20atmosphere%20and%20that's%20the%20reason%20why%20Boeing%20and%20NASA%20teams%20then%20opted%20to%20leave%20the%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20safely%20docked%20with%20the%20space%20station%20while%20they%20worked%20to%20learn%20as%20much%20as%20possible%20about%20those%20issues.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIt%20is%20not%20clear%20yet%20whether%20NASA%20will%20extend%20the%20maximum%20mission%20length%20to%2090%20days.%20Stich%20said%20officials%20must%20clear%20the%20battery%20life%20of%20the%20Starliner%20for%20that%20purpose.%20Although%20he%20noted%20that%20the%20batteries%20are%20being%20recharged%20at%20the%20space%20station%2C%20they%20should%20operate%20the%20same%20way%20after%2090%20days%20as%20they%20will%20for%20the%20first%2045%20days.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EThe%20spaceflight%20industry%20frequently%20experiences%20cost%20overruns%2C%20delays%20and%20unmet%20deadlines.%20However%2C%20Boeing%20has%20faced%20challenges%20that%20have%20stood%20out%2C%20particularly%20when%20the%20Starliner%20program%20is%20directly%20compared%20with%20SpaceX's%20Crew%20Dragon%2C%20CNN%20reported.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ECrew%20Dragon%2C%20which%20falls%20under%20the%20same%20NASA%20Commercial%20Crew%20Program%20for%20astronaut%20transportation%2C%20completed%20its%20first%20test%20flight%20in%202020%20and%20has%20been%20carrying%20out%20routine%20missions%20ever%20since.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ESpaceX%20did%20not%20have%20the%20benefit%20of%20designing%20the%20Crew%20Dragon%20spacecraft%20off%20the%20back%20of%20its%20Cargo%20Dragon%20vehicle%2C%20which%20for%20years%20sent%20supplies%20to%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%20before%20its%20successor%20started%20operating%20while%20Boeing%20designed%20Starliner%20from%20scratch.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENappi%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BWe've%20got%20a%20really%20good%20test%20flight%20that's%20been%20accomplished%20so%20far%2C%20and%20it's%20being%20viewed%20rather%20negatively.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20latest%20update%20regarding%20the%20ongoing%20space%20mission%2C%20the%20Expedition%2071%20crew%20members%20on%20Friday%20packed%20a%20US%20cargo%20craft%2C%20cleaned%20up%20the%20International%20Space%20Station%2C%20studied%20techniques%20of%20futuristic%20piloting%2C%20and%20carried%20out%20eye%20exams.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA's%20Boeing%20Crew%20Flight%20Test%20astronauts%20spent%20the%20day%20reconfiguring%20a%20space%20botany%20facility.%20In%20its%20live%20blog%2C%20NASA%20stated%2C%20%26quot%3B%20Robotics%20controllers%20are%20scheduled%20to%20detach%20the%20Cygnus%20space%20freighter%20from%20the%20Unity%20module%20on%20July%2012%20and%20release%20it%20into%20Earth%20orbit%20for%20disposal%20over%20the%20South%20Pacific%20Ocean%20ending%20a%20five-and-a-half-month%20mission%20at%20the%20orbital%20lab.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3ENASA%20Flight%20Engineer%20Matthew%20Dominick%20spent%20most%20of%20the%20time%20on%20Friday%20on%20loading%20trash%20and%20discarding%20gear%20inside%20the%20Cygnus%20with%20assistance%20from%20fellow%20NASA%20astronauts%20Jeanette%20Epps%20and%20Tracy%20C%20Dyson.%20Canadarm2%20robotic%20arm%20captured%20the%20Cygnus%20on%20February%201%2C%20with%20more%20than%208200%20pounds%20of%20science%20experiments%20and%20crew%20supplies.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEpps%20operated%20standard%20medical%20imaging%20gear%20found%20in%20an%20optometrist's%20office%20on%20Earth%20and%20peered%20into%20Dyson's%20eyes.%20She%20examined%20the%20cornea%2C%20retina%2C%20and%20lens%20of%20Dyson%20to%20help%20flight%20surgeons%20understand%20and%20counteract%20microgravity's%20effect%20on%20crew%20vision.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EEarlier%2C%20Dyson%20collected%20and%20stowed%20excess%20space%20station%20hardware%20for%20disposal.%20During%20the%20day%2C%20NASA%20Flight%20Engineer%20Mike%20Barratt%20routed%20cables%20and%20reprogrammed%20communications%20systems%20inside%20the%20Columbus%20laboratory%20module.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EHe%20stowed%20hardware%20and%20components%20used%20earlier%20in%20the%20week%20for%20advanced%20orbital%20plumbing%20in%20the%20Tranquility%20module's%20bathroom.%20Mike%20Barratt%20refilled%20supply%20kits%20in%20Columbus'%20two%20Human%20Research%20Facility%20racks%20with%20biomedical%20gear%2C%20including%20sample%20tubes%20and%20needles.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EOn%20Friday%2C%20Starliner's%20Commander%20and%20Pilot%2C%20Butch%20Wilmore%20and%20Sunita%20Williams%20in%20Kibo%20conducted%20space%20botany%20work.%20They%20removed%20the%20Plant%20Habitat%20growth%20chamber%20from%20Kibo's%20EXPRESS%20rack%2C%20replaced%20its%20camera%20and%20carbon%20dioxide%20sensors%2C%20then%20reinstalled%20the%20research%20device.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EIn%20the%20liveblog%2C%20NASA%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BNASA%20and%20Boeing%20continue%20to%20evaluate%20Starliner's%20propulsion%20system%20performance%20before%20returning%20to%20Earth%20from%20the%20orbiting%20lab.%20NASA%20and%20Boeing%20leaders%20participated%20in%20a%20media%20teleconference%20today%20to%20discuss%20Starliner%20and%20station%20operations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNASA%20is%20now%20targeting%20the%20end%20of%20July%20for%20the%20next%20spacewalk%20outside%20the%20space%20station.%20This%20change%20allows%20teams%20on%20the%20ground%20to%20continue%20to%20troubleshoot%20and%20understand%20the%20water%20leak%20in%20the%20service%20and%20cooling%20umbilical%20unit%20that%20forced%20an%20early%20end%20to%20a%20spacewalk%20on%20Monday%2C%20June%2024%2C%26quot%3B%20it%20added.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EFlight%20Engineer%20Nikolai%20Chub%20practiced%20planetary%20spacecraft%20and%20robotic%20piloting%20techniques%20future%20crew%20members%20and%20conducted%20two%20sessions%20of%20an%20investigation%20exploring%20ways%20to%20create%20new%20materials%20on%20the%20lunar%20surface.%3C%2Fp%3E%5Cn%3Cp%3EMeanwhile%2C%20Flight%20Engineer%20Alexander%20Grebenkin%20worked%20throughout%20the%20day%20inventorying%20medical%20kits%20and%20cleaning%20fans%20inside%20the%20Rassvet%20module%20and%20Station%20Commander%20Oleg%20Kononenko%20replaced%20thermal%20components%20in%20Roscosmos'%20life%20support%20hardware.%3Cbr%3E%5Cn%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%3Ci%3E(Except%20for%20the%20headline%2C%20this%20story%20has%20not%20been%20edited%20by%20NDTV%20staff%20and%20is%20published%20from%20a%20syndicated%20feed.)%3C%2Fi%3E%3C%2Fp%3E%22%2C%22published%22%3A1719639060000%2C%22visual%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fc.ndtvimg.com%2F2024-06%2Fnc9v6568_sunita-williams_625x300_25_June_24.jpeg%22%2C%22originID%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fastronaut-sunita-williams-may-have-to-wait-months-in-space-what-nasa-is-planning-now-5994474%22%2C%22summary%22%3A%22Projected%20to%20last%20only%20days%2C%20the%20first%20crewed%20test%20flight%20of%20Boeing's%20Starliner%20spacecraft%20with%20two%20astronauts%20onboard%20faces%20uncertainty%20with%20no%20exact%20return%20to%20Earth%20announced.%22%2C%22author%22%3A%22%22%2C%22engagement%22%3A0%2C%22canonicalUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fastronaut-sunita-williams-may-have-to-wait-months-in-space-what-nasa-is-planning-now-5994474%22%2C%22cdnAmpUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww-ndtv-com.cdn.ampproject.org%2Fc%2Fs%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fastronaut-sunita-williams-may-have-to-wait-months-in-space-what-nasa-is-planning-now-5994474%2Famp%2F1%22%2C%22ampUrl%22%3A%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.ndtv.com%2Fworld-news%2Fastronaut-sunita-williams-may-have-to-wait-months-in-space-what-nasa-is-planning-now-5994474%2Famp%2F1%22%7D%2C%7B%22title%22%3A%22Indian%20Woman%20Dries%20Clothes%20On%20Balcony%20Of%20Dubai%20Hot