BA%20tax-deferred%20account%20is%20one%20that%20often%20receives%20tax-deductible%20contributions%20but%20taxable%20withdrawals%20during%20retirement%2C%20like%20a%20pre-tax%20401(k)%20or%20traditional%20IRA.%20A%20tax-free%20growth%20account%20would%20be%20a%20Roth%20401(k)%2C%20Roth%20IRA%2C%20or%20HSA.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThis%20strategy%20allows%20you%20to%20pick%20and%20choose%20which%20accounts%20you%20draw%20from%20before%20and%20during%20your%20retirement%20to%20maximize%20your%20income%2C%20reduce%20your%20tax%20burden%2C%20and%20ensure%20continued%20growth%20of%20your%20money.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWorking%20with%20a%20tax%20advisor%20can%20help%20you%20be%20strategic%20about%20when%20and%20from%20which%20account%20to%20pay%20yourself%20in%20retirement%20to%20vastly%20reduce%20your%20tax%20bill%2C%26quot%3B%20Anastasio%20adds.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Ch2%3E%3Cstrong%3E5.%20Don't%20spend%20more%20as%20you%20make%20more%C2%A0%3C%2Fstrong%3E%3C%2Fh2%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20you%20get%20closer%20to%20retirement%20or%20you%20find%20yourself%20in%20a%20position%20of%20making%20more%20money%2C%20financial%20planner%20%3Ca%20rel%3D%5C%22noopener%5C%22%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fintrepideaglefinance.com%2Fabout%2Fabout-us%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ECharles%20H.%20Thomas%20III%3C%2Fa%3E%20says%20to%20beware%20of%20lifestyle%20inflation%2C%20since%20it's%20a%20risk%20that%20can%20throw%20your%20plans%20off%20track.%C2%A0%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BWhen%20you%20get%20a%20raise%20at%20work%2C%20it's%20tempting%20to%20spend%20that%20raise%20on%20a%20more%20comfortable%20lifestyle%2C%26quot%3B%20says%20Thomas.%20%26quot%3BInstead%2C%20think%20about%20how%20part%20of%20your%20increased%20salary%20can%20be%20saved%20or%20used%20to%20pay%20down%20some%20debt.%20Over%20time%2C%20the%20habit%20will%20get%20easier%20and%20you'll%20still%20have%20a%20comfortable%20lifestyle.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Caside%3E%3Cp%3E%3Cstrong%3EStart%20Saving%20for%20Goals%3A%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%3Ca%20h