%20that%20Congress%20itself%20created%20to%20respond%20quickly%20and%20efficiently%20to%20newly%20emerging%20problems%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Robert%20Hockett%2C%20a%20Cornell%20University%20professor%20of%20law%20and%20finance.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThanks%20to%20the%20recent%20SCOTUS%20rulings%2C%20the%20regulation%20of%20essentially%20all%20major%20industries%2C%20ranging%20from%20environmental%20protection%20to%20finance%20and%20public%20health%2C%20will%20be%20much%20tougher%20and%20could%20result%20in%20a%20more%20overburdened%20court%20system.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EBefore%20Friday's%20ruling%2C%20if%20the%20Environmental%20Protection%20Agency%2C%20for%20example%2C%20identified%20an%20oil%20company%20practice%20that%20unduly%20risked%20an%20oil%20spill%2C%20it%20would%20first%20issue%20a%20cease-and-desist%20letter.%20The%20oil%20company%20might%20then%20claim%20that%20the%20EPA%20has%20the%20facts%20wrong%20or%20lacks%20the%20regulatory%20authority%20to%20address%20the%20practice%2C%20Hockett%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThen%2C%20according%20to%20Hockett%2C%20the%20case%20would%20be%20heard%20by%20an%20administrative%20court.%20If%20the%20oil%20company%20disagreed%20with%20that%20administrative%20judge's%20ruling%2C%20it%20could%20appeal%20and%20ultimately%20land%20in%20a%20court%20%E2%80%94%20but%20wouldn't%20do%20so%20if%20it%20couldn't%20point%20to%20an%20obvious%20error%20by%20the%20administrative%20law%20judge%2C%20Hockett%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ENow%2C%20under%20the%20ruling%2C%20the%20case%20would%20go%20right%20to%20a%20federal%20court.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BNo%20ALJ%20%5BAdministrative%20Law%20Judge%5D.%20Straight%20to%20federal%20court.%20Court%20with%20overloaded%20docket%20scheduled%20hearing%20to%20the%20year%202035.%20Oil%20spills%20everywhere%20and%20renders%20North%20America%20uninhabitable%20in%20the%20meantime%20while%20we%20wait%2C%26quot%3B%20Hockett%20said%2C%20offering%20an%20extreme%20example.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20upshot%20of%20this%20is%20that%20all%20of%20the%20country's%20largest%20business%20firms%20in%20all%20of%20its%20major%20industries%20will%20go%20effectively%20unregulated%20or%20de-facto%20unregulated%20because%20Congress%20and%20the%20courts%20will%20not%20be%20able%20to%20keep%20up%20with%20the%20pace%20of%20change%20in%20our%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Hockett.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20legal%20expert%20likened%20the%20matter%20to%20a%20%26quot%3Brobber%20baron's%20dream.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThese%20two%20rulings%20largely%20amputate%20the%20two%20most%20important%20arms%20that%20our%20regulatory%20agencies%20use%20every%20day%20in%20overseeing%20our%20industrial%20economy%2C%26quot%3B%20Hockett%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EIn%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fscotus-chevron-doctrine-bidens-climate-policies-at-risk-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3Eoverturning%20the%20Chevron%20doctrine%3C%2Fa%3E%20in%20a%206-3%20decision%2C%20the%20high%20court%20has%20hamstrung%20federal%20agencies'%20regulatory%20powers.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20doctrine%2C%20established%20in%20the%201984%20Supreme%20Court%20case%20Chevron%20USA%20v.%20Natural%20Resources%20Defense%20Council%2C%20called%20for%20courts%20to%20defer%20to%20federal%20agencies'%20interpretations%20of%20ambiguous%20federal%20laws%20and%20statutes.%20It%20has%20been%20repeatedly%20used%20by%20the%20federal%20government%20in%20a%20wide%20range%20of%20cases.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EChief%20Justice%20John%20Roberts%2C%20in%20his%20opinion%2C%20wrote%20that%20the%20Chevron%20doctrine%20%26quot%3Bproved%20to%20be%20fundamentally%20misguided.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BPerhaps%20most%20fundamentally%2C%20Chevron's%20presumption%20is%20misguided%20because%20agencies%20have%20no%20special%20competence%20in%20resolving%20statutory%20ambiguities.%20Courts%20do%2C%26quot%3B%20Roberts%20wrote.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20chief%20justice%20continued%2C%20%26quot%3BCourts%20must%20exercise%20their%20independent%20judgment%20in%20deciding%20whether%20an%20agency%20has%20acted%20within%20its%20statutory%20authority.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThe%20overturning%20of%20the%20Chevron%20precedent%20and%20Thursday's%20%3Ca%20href%3D%5C%22https%3A%2F%2Fwww.businessinsider.com%2Fsupreme-court-strips-sec-enforcement-power-financial-fraud-jarkesy-2024-6%5C%22%20target%3D%5C%22_blank%5C%22%3ESEC%20v.%20Jarkesy%20decision%3C%2Fa%3E%20both%20involve%20cuts%20in%20the%20regulatory%20powers%20of%20federal%20agencies%2C%20%26quot%3Bwhich%20means%20reductions%20in%20the%20power%20of%20the%20executive%20branch%20of%20government%20and%20an%20increase%20in%20the%20power%20of%20the%20judicial%20branch%2C%26quot%3B%20said%20Jonathan%20Siegel%2C%20a%20professor%20of%20law%20at%20George%20Washington%20University.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EAs%20a%20result%2C%20over%20the%20long%20term%2C%20Siegel%20said%2C%20%26quot%3BIt%20will%20be%20more%20difficult%20for%20the%20government%20to%20enforce%20many%20statutes%2C%20and%20therefore%2C%20there%20will%20be%20more%20violations.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BParticularly%20in%20terms%20of%20businesses%2C%20they%20decide%20what%20to%20do%20based%20not%20only%20on%20what's%20legal%20and%20what's%20illegal%2C%20but%20what%20is%20the%20likelihood%20that%20they%20will%20actually%20suffer%20a%20penalty%20if%20they%20do%20something%20illegal%2C%26quot%3B%20he%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ESiegel%20explained%20that%20the%20decision%20in%20SEC%20v.%20Jarkesy%20has%20the%20%26quot%3Bpotential%20to%20affect%20innumerable%20agency%20proceedings.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EUp%20until%20Thursday%2C%20the%20SEC%20had%20two%20ways%20of%20pursuing%20fraud%20cases.%20It%20could%20sue%20in%20federal%20court%2C%20or%20it%20could%20bring%20an%20%26quot%3Badministrative%20proceeding%26quot%3B%20in%20its%20own%20in-house%20court%2C%20where%20it%20appoints%20its%20own%20judges%20and%20the%20cases%20have%20no%20juries.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERoberts%20wrote%20in%20the%20decision%20that%20the%20latter%20method%20violated%20the%20Seventh%20Amendment%20of%20the%20US%20Constitution%2C%20which%20protects%20the%20right%20to%20a%20jury%20trial.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BIt's%20certainly%20the%20case%20that%20the%20court%20and%20some%20individual%20justices%20even%20more%20strongly%20have%20expressed%20distaste%20for%20the%20amount%20of%20power%20administrative%20agencies%20have%2C%20and%20several%20decisions%20that%20the%20court%20has%20come%20down%20within%20the%20last%20few%20years%20have%20the%20effect%20of%20reducing%20that%20power%20and%20increasing%20the%20power%20of%20courts%2C%26quot%3B%20Siegel%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3ERachel%20Weintraub%2C%20the%20executive%20director%20of%20the%20regulation%20advocacy%20group%20Coalition%20for%20Sensible%20Safeguards%2C%20said%20that%20the%20common%20thread%20between%20the%20two%20decisions%20%26quot%3Bis%20that%20it%20is%20the%20manifestation%20of%20a%20conservative%20quest%20to%20minimize%20the%20role%20of%20the%20federal%20government.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3E%26quot%3BThe%20public%20expects%20government%20to%20do%20certain%20things.%20It%20expects%20the%20government%20to%20ensure%20that%20roads%20are%20safe%20and%20toasters%20don't%20explode%2C%20and%20that%20the%20water%20coming%20from%20our%20faucet%20doesn't%20cause%20our%20families%20harm%2C%20and%20that%20there%20are%20protections%20in%20workplaces%2C%20and%20that%20our%20marketplaces%20are%20fair%2C%20and%20that%20there%20will%20be%20consequences%20if%20entities%20scam%20us%2C%26quot%3B%20Weintraub%20said.%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EThese%20factors%2C%20said%20Weintraub%2C%20%26quot%3Bcould%20be%20at%20stake%20if%20judges%20replace%20agency%20expertise%20with%20their%20own%20positions.%26quot%3B%3C%2Fp%3E%3Cp%3EJesse%20Panuccio%2C%20who%20served%20as%20US%20acting%20associate%20attorney%20general%20in%20the%20Trump%20administration%2C%20was%20less%20alarmed%20by%20the%20recent%20SCOTUS%20decisions%2C%20saying%20%26quot%3Bagencies%20still%20have%20vast%20delegations%20of%20