0with%20kindness.%E2%80%9D%20%3C%2Fstrong%3EShaming%20and%20yelling%20harm%20a%20child%E2%80%99s%20mental%20well-being%20and%20development.%20Parents%20often%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CBut%20we%20don%E2%80%99t%20know%20any%20other%20way.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIn%20these%20sessions%20they%20have%20moved%20from%20saying%2C%20%E2%80%9CTurn%20off%20that%20video%20game%20right%20now%2C%20you%20useless%20fellow.%20You%20never%20listen%2C%E2%80%9D%20to%20setting%20limits%20with%20sensitivity.%20They%20now%20say%2C%20%E2%80%9CI%20know%20you%E2%80%99re%20enjoying%20that%20game%20but%20your%20time%20is%20up%2C%20and%20I%E2%80%99m%20sorry%20I%20need%20to%20switch%20this%20off%20for%20you%20as%20you%20are%20finding%20it%20hard%20to%20stop.%E2%80%9D%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EIt%20takes%20a%20while%20to%20learn%20these%20skills%20but%20when%20they%20do%2C%20the%20parents%20feel%20like%20they%E2%80%99ve%20found%20a%20key%20to%20a%20new%20world.%20More%20importantly%2C%20parents%20become%20aware%20that%20the%20shift%20has%20led%20to%20their%20children%20feeling%20emotionally%20safe%20with%20them%20and%20having%20better%20self-esteem.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn%3Col%20start%3D%5C%2210%5C%22%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3E%3Cstrong%3EIt%E2%80%99s%20me%20who%20needs%20to%20change%2C%20not%20my%20child%3C%2Fstrong%3E%20%E2%80%93%20At%20the%20end%20of%20our%20parenting%20courses%2C%20this%20is%20the%20most%20common%20observation%20parents%20make.%20The%20realisation%20that%20stands%20out%20the%20most%20is%20that%20it%E2%80%99s%20not%20about%20fixing%20the%20child%20but%20about%20working%20on%20yourself%20which%20then%20brings%20out%20the%20best%20in%20your%20child.%C2%A0%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Fol%3E%5Cn%3Cul%3E%5Cn%3Cli%3EWhen%20parents%20become%20more%20empathetic%2C%20patient%2C%20and%20understanding%2C%20they%20invariably%20see%20a%20positive%20transformation%20in%20their%20child%E2%80%99s%20behaviour.%3C%2Fli%3E%5Cn%3C%2Ful%3E%5Cn